<br>
Each sage asks that you take the research from each of the other two sages and give it to one or the other of his assistants, depending on which sage the research is taken from.  Its all very symmetrical.<br>
<br>
So for each piece of research obtained, there are two paths to go with it.<br>
<br>
Items from Gunyth can go to either Winon or Acomar<br>
Items from Balic can go to either Onerin or Boloen<br>
Items from Xelrin can go to either Tenada or Xesri<br>
<br>
Which path is the correct path?<br>
<br>
I think people have taken the items from Gunyth (the items with charges) and given them to Acomar for worthless rewards.  Has anyone tried giving one of these items to Winon instead?  Maybe Winon turns it into a new Rune or a Page, which will be used for further processing.<br>
<br>
The fact that some of the assistants take your items in return for a gem and XP indicates that giving them items is at least on the right path, no?<br>
<br>
Some of the assistants mention that you have to get 'the basics' down first.  This is associated with another quest, the quest that extends the Planar Traveller Handbook quest.<br>
<br>
Maybe if someone could get the Planar Travellers Handbook, then do the quest that results in the Basic Magic Handbook, and hold that while doing the turnins to the assistants, a different reaction may take place?<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts.<br>
<br>
Erun<br>
